  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic V&V 40 credibility package for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Thirteen credibility factors are assessed; seven carry achieved levels at or near required levels, six remain epistemic gaps. A validation result referencing the Bludszuweit (1995) scalar stress hemolysis correlation is included without a comparedAgainst link; the narrative treats the correlation benchmark as directly applicable to the VAD operating envelope without noting that the underlying experimental data were collected on a Couette-flow device at shear exposures well below the pulsatile, high-shear regime of the centrifugal VAD. Decision outcome recorded as Accepted for adversarial-sample purposes.",
